"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"\\n# Skip Go Fast (`Instant Deposit`)\\n\\nSkip Go Fast is a **decentralized bridging protocol**, developed by **Skip**, that enables **rapid and secure cross-chain transactions** across major blockchain ecosystems such as Ethereum, Cosmos, and Solana. Go Fast accelerates cross-chain actions by up to 25 times, **reducing onboarding times from 10+ minutes to seconds**. Learn more [here](https://docs.skip.build/go/advanced-transfer/go-fast#go-fast).\\n\\n## Supported Chains & Assets\\n\\n- **Chains:** Ethereum Mainnet, Arbitrum, Avalanche, Base, Optimism, Polygon\\n- **Assets:** USDC, ETH, POL\\n\\n## Min & Max Transfer Sizes\\n\\n| Source Chain     | Min Transfer (USD) | Max Transfer (USD) |\\n| ---------------- | ------------------ | ------------------ |\\n| Ethereum Mainnet | 50                 | 25,000             |\\n| Arbitrum         | 1                  | 25,000             |\\n| Base             | 1                  | 25,000             |\\n| Optimism         | 1                  | 25,000             |\\n| Polygon          | 1                  | 25,000             |\\n\\nFor the latest Minimum & Maximum Transfer Sizes, checkout the Skip API [documents](https://docs.skip.build/go/advanced-transfer/go-fast#what-are-the-minimum-and-maximum-transfer-sizes-for-go-fast%3F). \\n\\n:::info\\nIf starting with an asset that is not USDC, Skip Go will swap the asset to USDC on the source chain, and the post-swap amount is used to determine if it falls within the min/max transfer size limits.\\n:::\\n\\n## Fees\\n\\n:::info\\n- As of 24/6 Ethereum deposits > $100 route via skip go fast by default and are free of fees.\\n- As of 8/7 EVM L2 deposits > $20 route via skip go fast by default and are free of fees.\\nAll other routes go via skip regular\\n:::\\n\\nAll Skip Go Fast `10 bps` on the transfer size \\\\+ source chain fee:\\n\\n\\n\\n| Source Chain     | Fee (USD)                          |\\n| ---------------- | ---------------------------------- |\\n| Ethereum Mainnet | \\\\~$2.5 (depends on gas fees)       |\\n| Arbitrum         | \\\\~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees) |\\n| Base             | \\\\~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees) |\\n| Optimism         | \\\\~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees) |\\n| Polygon          | \\\\~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees) |\\n\\nFor the latest source chain fees, checkout the Skip API [documents](https://docs.skip.build/go/advanced-transfer/go-fast#what-is-the-fee-model-for-go-fast%3F). \\n\\n## Process Flow (Deposit)\\n\\n1. **Connect your wallet** to the dYdX interface and navigate to the \\\"Deposit\\\" section\\n2. **Enter the amount** you wish to transfer (ensure it meets minimum requirements)\\n3. **Choose the source chain and asset** you wish to deposit\\n4. **Review the transaction details** including estimated fees and finality time\\n5. **Confirm and sign** the transaction from your wallet\\n6. **Skip Go Fast protocol's solvers** monitor for confirmation of fund arrival at Noble\\n   - This process relies on Skip's decentralized solver network\\n   - If your source token is not USDC, an automatic swap occurs via integrated DEXs\\n7. Once confirmed, funds are automatically sent to dYdX Chain via IBC transfer\\n   - This step uses IBC relayers to complete the cross-chain transfer\\n8. Final step Funds are moved from the main account to the subaccount for trading\\n   - This internal transfer is handled by dYdX Chain’s infrastructure\\n\\n\\n## How Skip Go Fast Works\\n\\nSkip Go Fast uses a solver-based approach to achieve near-instant finality:\\n\\n:::steps\\n#### **User Intent Submission**\\n   - When you initiate a transfer, you call the `submitOrder` function on the protocol contract\\n   - This broadcasts your intent to transfer assets across chains\\n   - Your intent specifies the assets, destination address, and any additional message payload\\n#### **Solver Network**\\n   - Permissionless participants called \\\"solvers\\\" watch for these intents\\n   - Solvers evaluate whether they can fulfill your intent based on:\\n     - Their available liquidity on the destination chain\\n     - Potential reward for fulfilling the intent\\n   - When a solver agrees to fulfill your intent, they use their own capital to front the assets\\n#### **Instant Fulfillment**\\n   - The solver calls the `fillOrder` function on the destination chain\\n   - This transfers the specified assets and processes any additional actions\\n   - From your perspective, the assets appear on the destination chain almost instantly\\n#### **Settlement Process**\\n   - After fulfilling your transfer, the solver initiates settlement to recover their fronted assets\\n   - The protocol verifies the solver's actions via a cross-chain messaging system\\n   - Once confirmed, the solver receives their assets back plus any earned fees\\n   - This settlement happens in the background and doesn't affect your user experience.\\n::::\\n\\n\\n## Example deposit\\n Base → dYdX via Skip Go Fast\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n    \\\"operations\\\": [\\n        {\\n            \\\"evm_swap\\\": {\\n                \\\"from_chain_id\\\": \\\"8453\\\",\\n                \\\"denom_in\\\": \\\"base-native\\\",\\n                \\\"denom_out\\\": \\\"USDC\\\",\\n                \\\"amount_in\\\": \\\"10511954965182950\\\",\\n                \\\"amount_out\\\": \\\"21430265\\\",\\n                \\\"swap_venues\\\": [\\n                    {\\\"name\\\": \\\"base-uniswap\\\"}\\n                ]\\n            }\\n        },\\n        {\\n            \\\"cctp_transfer\\\": {\\n                \\\"from_chain_id\\\": \\\"8453\\\",\\n                \\\"to_chain_id\\\": \\\"noble-1\\\",\\n                \\\"denom_in\\\": \\\"USDC\\\",\\n                \\\"denom_out\\\": \\\"uusdc\\\",\\n                \\\"bridge_id\\\": \\\"CCTP\\\"\\n            }\\n        },\\n        {\\n            \\\"transfer\\\": {\\n                \\\"from_chain_id\\\": \\\"noble-1\\\",\\n                \\\"to_chain_id\\\": \\\"dydx-mainnet-1\\\",\\n                \\\"denom_in\\\": \\\"uusdc\\\",\\n                \\\"denom_out\\\": \\\"ibc/USDC\\\",\\n                \\\"bridge_id\\\": \\\"IBC\\\"\\n            }\\n        }\\n    ]\\n}\\n```\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast#skip-go-fast-instant-deposit\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>Skip Go Fast is a <strong>decentralized bridging protocol</strong>, developed by <strong>Skip</strong>, that enables <strong>rapid and secure cross-chain transactions</strong> across major blockchain ecosystems such as Ethereum, Cosmos, and Solana. Go Fast accelerates cross-chain actions by up to 25 times, <strong>reducing onboarding times from 10+ minutes to seconds</strong>. Learn more <a href=\\\"https://docs.skip.build/go/advanced-transfer/go-fast#go-fast\\\">here</a>.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast.mdx#skip-go-fast-instant-deposit\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nSkip Go Fast is a decentralized bridging protocol, developed by Skip, that enables rapid and secure cross-chain transactions across major blockchain ecosystems such as Ethereum, Cosmos, and Solana. Go Fast accelerates cross-chain actions by up to 25 times, reducing onboarding times from 10+ minutes to seconds. Learn more here.\\n\",\"title\":\"Skip Go Fast (Instant Deposit)\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast#supported-chains--assets\",\"html\":\"\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Chains:</strong> Ethereum Mainnet, Arbitrum, Avalanche, Base, Optimism, Polygon</li>\\n<li><strong>Assets:</strong> USDC, ETH, POL</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast.mdx#supported-chains--assets\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\\nChains: Ethereum Mainnet, Arbitrum, Avalanche, Base, Optimism, Polygon\\nAssets: USDC, ETH, POL\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Supported Chains &amp; Assets\",\"titles\":[\"Skip Go Fast (Instant Deposit)\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast#min--max-transfer-sizes\",\"html\":\"\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Source Chain</th><th>Min Transfer (USD)</th><th>Max Transfer (USD)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Ethereum Mainnet</td><td>50</td><td>25,000</td></tr><tr><td>Arbitrum</td><td>1</td><td>25,000</td></tr><tr><td>Base</td><td>1</td><td>25,000</td></tr><tr><td>Optimism</td><td>1</td><td>25,000</td></tr><tr><td>Polygon</td><td>1</td><td>25,000</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n<p>For the latest Minimum &amp; Maximum Transfer Sizes, checkout the Skip API <a href=\\\"https://docs.skip.build/go/advanced-transfer/go-fast#what-are-the-minimum-and-maximum-transfer-sizes-for-go-fast%3F\\\">documents</a>.</p>\\n<aside data-callout=\\\"info\\\"><p>If starting with an asset that is not USDC, Skip Go will swap the asset to USDC on the source chain, and the post-swap amount is used to determine if it falls within the min/max transfer size limits.</p></aside>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast.mdx#min--max-transfer-sizes\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nSource ChainMin Transfer (USD)Max Transfer (USD)Ethereum Mainnet5025,000Arbitrum125,000Base125,000Optimism125,000Polygon125,000\\nFor the latest Minimum &amp; Maximum Transfer Sizes, checkout the Skip API documents.\\nIf starting with an asset that is not USDC, Skip Go will swap the asset to USDC on the source chain, and the post-swap amount is used to determine if it falls within the min/max transfer size limits.\\n\",\"title\":\"Min &amp; Max Transfer Sizes\",\"titles\":[\"Skip Go Fast (Instant Deposit)\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast#fees\",\"html\":\"\\n<aside data-callout=\\\"info\\\"><ul>\\n<li>As of 24/6 Ethereum deposits &gt; $100 route via skip go fast by default and are free of fees.</li>\\n<li>As of 8/7 EVM L2 deposits &gt; $20 route via skip go fast by default and are free of fees.\\nAll other routes go via skip regular</li>\\n</ul></aside>\\n<p>All Skip Go Fast <code>10 bps</code> on the transfer size + source chain fee:</p>\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Source Chain</th><th>Fee (USD)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Ethereum Mainnet</td><td>~$2.5 (depends on gas fees)</td></tr><tr><td>Arbitrum</td><td>~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees)</td></tr><tr><td>Base</td><td>~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees)</td></tr><tr><td>Optimism</td><td>~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees)</td></tr><tr><td>Polygon</td><td>~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees)</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n<p>For the latest source chain fees, checkout the Skip API <a href=\\\"https://docs.skip.build/go/advanced-transfer/go-fast#what-is-the-fee-model-for-go-fast%3F\\\">documents</a>.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast.mdx#fees\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\\nAs of 24/6 Ethereum deposits &gt; $100 route via skip go fast by default and are free of fees.\\nAs of 8/7 EVM L2 deposits &gt; $20 route via skip go fast by default and are free of fees.\\nAll other routes go via skip regular\\n\\nAll Skip Go Fast 10 bps on the transfer size + source chain fee:\\nSource ChainFee (USD)Ethereum Mainnet~$2.5 (depends on gas fees)Arbitrum~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees)Base~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees)Optimism~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees)Polygon~$0.01-$0.1 (depends on gas fees)\\nFor the latest source chain fees, checkout the Skip API documents.\\n\",\"title\":\"Fees\",\"titles\":[\"Skip Go Fast (Instant Deposit)\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast#process-flow-deposit\",\"html\":\"\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Connect your wallet</strong> to the dYdX interface and navigate to the &quot;Deposit&quot; section</li>\\n<li><strong>Enter the amount</strong> you wish to transfer (ensure it meets minimum requirements)</li>\\n<li><strong>Choose the source chain and asset</strong> you wish to deposit</li>\\n<li><strong>Review the transaction details</strong> including estimated fees and finality time</li>\\n<li><strong>Confirm and sign</strong> the transaction from your wallet</li>\\n<li><strong>Skip Go Fast protocol&#x27;s solvers</strong> monitor for confirmation of fund arrival at Noble\\n<ul>\\n<li>This process relies on Skip&#x27;s decentralized solver network</li>\\n<li>If your source token is not USDC, an automatic swap occurs via integrated DEXs</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li>Once confirmed, funds are automatically sent to dYdX Chain via IBC transfer\\n<ul>\\n<li>This step uses IBC relayers to complete the cross-chain transfer</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li>Final step Funds are moved from the main account to the subaccount for trading\\n<ul>\\n<li>This internal transfer is handled by dYdX Chain’s infrastructure</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n</ol>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast.mdx#process-flow-deposit\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\\nConnect your wallet to the dYdX interface and navigate to the &quot;Deposit&quot; section\\nEnter the amount you wish to transfer (ensure it meets minimum requirements)\\nChoose the source chain and asset you wish to deposit\\nReview the transaction details including estimated fees and finality time\\nConfirm and sign the transaction from your wallet\\nSkip Go Fast protocol&#x27;s solvers monitor for confirmation of fund arrival at Noble\\n\\nThis process relies on Skip&#x27;s decentralized solver network\\nIf your source token is not USDC, an automatic swap occurs via integrated DEXs\\n\\n\\nOnce confirmed, funds are automatically sent to dYdX Chain via IBC transfer\\n\\nThis step uses IBC relayers to complete the cross-chain transfer\\n\\n\\nFinal step Funds are moved from the main account to the subaccount for trading\\n\\nThis internal transfer is handled by dYdX Chain’s infrastructure\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Process Flow (Deposit)\",\"titles\":[\"Skip Go Fast (Instant Deposit)\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast#how-skip-go-fast-works\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Skip Go Fast uses a solver-based approach to achieve near-instant finality:</p>\\n<div data-vocs-steps=\\\"true\\\"><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast.mdx#how-skip-go-fast-works\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nSkip Go Fast uses a solver-based approach to achieve near-instant finality:\\n\",\"title\":\"How Skip Go Fast Works\",\"titles\":[\"Skip Go Fast (Instant Deposit)\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast#user-intent-submission\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>When you initiate a transfer, you call the <code>submitOrder</code> function on the protocol contract</li>\\n<li>This broadcasts your intent to transfer assets across chains</li>\\n<li>Your intent specifies the assets, destination address, and any additional message payload</li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast.mdx#user-intent-submission\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nWhen you initiate a transfer, you call the submitOrder function on the protocol contract\\nThis broadcasts your intent to transfer assets across chains\\nYour intent specifies the assets, destination address, and any additional message payload\\n\",\"title\":\"User Intent Submission\",\"titles\":[\"Skip Go Fast (Instant Deposit)\",\"How Skip Go Fast Works\",null]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast#solver-network\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>Permissionless participants called &quot;solvers&quot; watch for these intents</li>\\n<li>Solvers evaluate whether they can fulfill your intent based on:\\n<ul>\\n<li>Their available liquidity on the destination chain</li>\\n<li>Potential reward for fulfilling the intent</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li>When a solver agrees to fulfill your intent, they use their own capital to front the assets</li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast.mdx#solver-network\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nPermissionless participants called &quot;solvers&quot; watch for these intents\\nSolvers evaluate whether they can fulfill your intent based on:\\n\\nTheir available liquidity on the destination chain\\nPotential reward for fulfilling the intent\\n\\n\\nWhen a solver agrees to fulfill your intent, they use their own capital to front the assets\\n\",\"title\":\"Solver Network\",\"titles\":[\"Skip Go Fast (Instant Deposit)\",\"How Skip Go Fast Works\",null]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast#instant-fulfillment\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>The solver calls the <code>fillOrder</code> function on the destination chain</li>\\n<li>This transfers the specified assets and processes any additional actions</li>\\n<li>From your perspective, the assets appear on the destination chain almost instantly</li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast.mdx#instant-fulfillment\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe solver calls the fillOrder function on the destination chain\\nThis transfers the specified assets and processes any additional actions\\nFrom your perspective, the assets appear on the destination chain almost instantly\\n\",\"title\":\"Instant Fulfillment\",\"titles\":[\"Skip Go Fast (Instant Deposit)\",\"How Skip Go Fast Works\",null]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast#settlement-process\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>After fulfilling your transfer, the solver initiates settlement to recover their fronted assets</li>\\n<li>The protocol verifies the solver&#x27;s actions via a cross-chain messaging system</li>\\n<li>Once confirmed, the solver receives their assets back plus any earned fees</li>\\n<li>This settlement happens in the background and doesn&#x27;t affect your user experience.</li>\\n</ul></div></div>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast.mdx#settlement-process\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nAfter fulfilling your transfer, the solver initiates settlement to recover their fronted assets\\nThe protocol verifies the solver&#x27;s actions via a cross-chain messaging system\\nOnce confirmed, the solver receives their assets back plus any earned fees\\nThis settlement happens in the background and doesn&#x27;t affect your user experience.\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Settlement Process\",\"titles\":[\"Skip Go Fast (Instant Deposit)\",\"How Skip Go Fast Works\",null]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/skipgofast#example-deposit\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Base → dYdX via Skip Go Fast</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">{</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">    &quot;operations&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: [</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">        {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">            &quot;evm_swap&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">                &quot;from_chain_id&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;8453&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">                &quot;denom_in&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;base-native&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color